i) The data lake has no predefined schema before storage, which allows for greater flexibility compared to a data warehouse. 
When it comes to work with multiple data sources in different formats, this flexibility is important in choosing the best storage 
format, making a Data Lake the ideal choice in such cases.

ii) In this case, the data warehouse is the best option because its structure (schema) is well-defined and documented.

iii) Data Warehouse, because, as stated in the text, its structure (schema) is defined before storage. 
For this reason, any changes can be complicated once it has been established.
